{"id": "1506917786948206643", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "type": 19, "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "author_bot": false, "content": "Okay so I tried to check out Crowdin, and it seems *really expensive.* The free options don't sound like they scale to a project of this size.\n\n> **What are hosted words?**\n> Hosted words are the number of words that should be translated multiplied by the number of the project's target languages. For example, if you upload a file with 500 words to a project with 10 target languages, you'll have 5,000 hosted words (500 × 10).\nThe free plan allows for a project up to 60,000 hosted words. That's... Not even enough for my Wheels of Destiny file, which is 105,265 words.", "timestamp": "2026-05-21T07:13:17.587000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["265494179222650891"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1506450220966215782", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
