{"id": "1506921249782235136", "channel_id": "1402941858606219294", "type": 19, "author_id": "265494179222650891", "author_name": "haps", "author_bot": false, "content": "If we are talking about free plans, then only GitLocalize comes to my mind <:RozaThink:671125370719830056> \nIt's not only native, but still helpful:\n- Tracks modifications in the source repository in real-time and pushes translated content back via structured pull requests\n- Multi-format file support\n- Monitored source files trigger visual flags when changes, additions, or deletions occurs, highlighting exactly what needs updating\n- Translation Memory (which is best friend for translators!!)\nhttps://gitlocalize.com/", "timestamp": "2026-05-21T07:27:03.191000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["183782216353054720"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [{"type": "link", "title": "GitLocalize - Continuous Localization for GitHub Projects", "url": "https://gitlocalize.com/", "description": "GitLocalize is a powerful continuous localization platform for GitHub projects"}], "reply_to": "1506918190293319752", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
